  </Placemark>
  <Placemark>
    <name>Lon C. Hill Home</name>
    <description><![CDATA[Harlingen Arts and Heritage Museum<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> 2425 Boxwood St., Harlingen<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> City's first home, built 1904, by the founder, Lon C. Hill, promoter of railroads and irrigation to the lower Rio Grande Valley. Climate-adapted Victorian house. Here valley pioneers met and planned important developments. Recorded Texas Historic Landmark - 1980]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-97.667945,26.217769,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
